  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  1.Chronic hepatitis B.

          -  2.defined by an acute deterioration in Transaminase greater than or equal to 10 NUT
             time over14 days.

          -  3.development of jaundice (serum bilirubin greater than or equal to 5mg/dl).

          -  more than one of the below criteria：

          -  4.development of coagulopathy(INR≥1.5).

          -  5.development of hepatic encephalopathy.

          -  6.development of renal insufficiency(serum creatinine ≥ 2 mg/dl ).

          -  7.Hepatic narrowing.

          -  8.development of massive ascites or peritonitis.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  1.Patients who have hepatocellular carcinoma.

          -  2.Patients who have autoimmune disease.

          -  3.Patients with significant co-morbid illnesses such as cardiovascular or respiratory
             or intrinsic renal diseases which by themselves may have a bearing on the outcome.

          -  4.Patients who have disseminated intravascular coagulation.

          -  5.Drug allergy.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
